    "In the first two self-calibration stages, the imaging step used closure data (closure amplitudes and phases) and visibility amplitudes.",
    "The imaging used closure data and complex visibilities for the final two self-calibration stages.",
    "Similar to eht-imaging, SMILI also performed all rounds of self-calibration on scan-averaged timescales.",
    "We employ THEMIS, a generic modular parameter estimation framework specifically developed to compare parameterized models with VLBI data produced by the EHT (Broderick et al. 2020a).",
    "The basic THEMIS image model aims to reproduce the on-sky brightness distribution and the time-dependent complex station gains."
